s groundbreaking publication.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aCity planning. 0aSustainable architecture. 0aSustainable development. 0aSustainable urban development. 0aUrban ecology (Sociology). 4aNachhaltigkeit. 4aQuartiere. 4aQuartiersentwicklung. 4aStadtplanung. 7aARCHITECTURE / Professional Practice.2bisacsh1 aAltmann, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAnders, Stephan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaumüller, Jürgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBott, Helmut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBott, Helmut, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBusch, Sigrid, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBöttge, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChurch, Dominic, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEl-Shahat, Manal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErl, Thorsten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGantner, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGrassi, Gregor, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGrassl, Gregor C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarlander, Tilman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHauber, Gerhard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaun, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenckel, Dietrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHildebrandt, Olaf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aL